: train_1_5 train test .

set.seed(1234)
splits <- train_1_5 %>% initial_split(prop = 0.7, strata = weekly_sales)
train2r <- training(splits)
test2r <- testing(splits)
train2r <- train2r %>% select(weekly_sales,is_holiday,year,month,day,fuel_price,cpi,unemployment,mean_storedept_month,mean_storedept_day,mean_storedept_is_holiday,mean_storedept_is_size )
test2r <- test2r %>% select(weekly_sales,is_holiday,year,month,day,fuel_price,cpi,unemployment,mean_storedept_month,mean_storedept_day,mean_storedept_is_holiday,mean_storedept_is_size )
train2r %>% is.na() %>% colSums()

rec <- train2r %>% 
  recipe(weekly_sales ~ .) %>%
  step_BoxCox(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%  
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors()) # %>%  step_dummy(all_nominal())

bake 

pre <- prep(rec)
train2 <- bake(pre, new_data=NULL)
test2 <- bake(pre, new_data=test2r)
